<!--
  OMX-F (follower) — self-contained description for the socket_hardware_interface
  stack. Geometry/inertials transcribed from ROBOTIS open_manipulator_description
  (omx_f_arm.urdf.xacro / omx_f.urdf.xacro); Gazebo includes dropped and the
  <ros2_control> block rewritten to drive the motors through
  socket_hardware_interface/SocketSystemInterface (a vendored DYNAMIXEL driver
  process on the other end of the Unix socket) instead of ROBOTIS'
  dynamixel_hardware_interface.

  UNITS: this driver's position/velocity interfaces are DEGREES / deg-s (not
  radians). The URDF <limit> tags below stay in radians per the URDF spec (used
  by robot_state_publisher/TF only) — the two are intentionally decoupled.

  Motor map (DYNAMIXEL X-series, IDs 11-16):
    joint1=11 extended_position (multi-turn)   joint2-5=12-15 position (single-turn)
    gripper_joint_1=16 current_based_position (force-limited grip)
-->
